===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In oracle bone and bronze inscriptions, {{liushu|p|nocap=yes}}: a granary, depicting its roof ({{zh-l|*亼}}), a door ({{zh-l|*戶}}), and a pit for storing grain ({{zh-l|*口}}). Alternatively an {{Han compound|合|戶|t1=gather|t2=door|ls=ic|nocap=yes}} – a warehouse. The component {{zh-l|*戶}} corrupted into {{zh-l|*𠁣}} in Qin bamboo slips. This form was inherited in small seal script and was misinterpreted as cognate with the unrelated {{zh-l|*食}} in the {{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}.

===Etymology===
From {{der|zh|sit-pro|*tsaŋ|t=to conceal}}.

